<section class="manifesto container" id="manifesto" tabindex="-1">
  <h2 class="display statement reveal">
    Your engineers shouldn’t need a&nbsp;glossary<span class="dot">.</span>
  </h2>

  <div class="body reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.1s">
    <p>
      Most software shops won’t touch the psychedelic industry — the
      compliance surface scares them off. The ones that will tend not to
      understand it: they’ll ship you a beautiful booking flow that violates
      your own protocol in three places.
    </p>
    <p>
      Elliodelics is fluent in both worlds: fifteen years leading engineering
      teams on one side, graduate work in psychedelics and consciousness
      studies on the other. You should never have to translate your work for
      the people building its infrastructure.
    </p>
    <p>
      And the stakes here are different. A leaked customer list is a bad week
      for a SaaS company; for a clinic or a retreat it’s people’s medical and
      legal exposure. Privacy gets designed in at the first schema, not
      bolted on before an audit.
    </p>
  </div>

  <figure class="diagram reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.15s">
    <svg
      viewBox="45 0 290 185"
      role="img"
      aria-label="The skeletal structure of psilocybin, drawn as a line schematic"
    >
      <g class="stroke">
        <!-- indole: benzene ring -->
        <path d="M60 92 L100 69 L140 92 L140 138 L100 161 L60 138 Z" />
        <!-- aromatic inner bonds -->
        <path d="M104 78 L133 95" />
        <path d="M133 135 L104 152" />
        <path d="M67 132 L67 98" />
        <!-- fused pyrrole -->
        <path d="M140 92 L183 79 L210 115 L183 151 L140 138" />
        <!-- C2=C3 double bond -->
        <path d="M186 88 L206 114" />
        <!-- side chain: C3 → CH2 → CH2 → N -->
        <path d="M183 79 L212 52 L246 66 L272 46" />
        <!-- N-methyls -->
        <path d="M287 40 L316 50" />
        <path d="M282 32 L288 12" />
        <!-- 4-phosphoryloxy bond -->
        <path d="M100 69 L100 44" />
      </g>
      <g class="label">
        <text x="183" y="168">NH</text>
        <text x="279" y="47">N</text>
        <text x="100" y="34">OPO₃H₂</text>
      </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption class="mono">fig. 01 — psilocybin, as a chemist draws it</figcaption>
  </figure>
</section>

<style>
  .manifesto {
    padding-block: var(--space-section);
  }

  /* scroll target only — the ring belongs on controls, not sections */
  .manifesto:focus-visible { outline: none; }

  .statement {
    font-size: var(--text-h2);
    max-width: 16ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .dot { color: var(--acid); }

  .body {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin-block: 3rem 0;
    margin-inline-start: auto;
  }
  .body p { margin: 0; }
  .body p + p { margin-block-start: 1.2em; }

  .diagram {
    margin: clamp(4rem, 9vh, 7rem) 0 0;
  }

  .diagram svg {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    max-width: 23rem;
  }

  .stroke path,
  .stroke rect {
    fill: none;
    stroke: var(--ink);
    stroke-width: 1.5;
    stroke-linecap: round;
    stroke-linejoin: round;
  }

  .label text {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    fill: var(--ink);
    text-anchor: middle;
  }

  figcaption {
    margin-block-start: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
  }
</style>
